curl localhost
curl <website> -> Return response content website
curl -i <website> -> Returns response header information like 200 OK, content/type, length, server info etc..

GET:
curl https://saifnaqvi.com/methods -> Send get data to website

POST:
curl -d "first=Saif&last=Naqvi" https://saifnaqvi.com/methods -> Send post (-d) data to website

PUT:
curl -X PUT -d "first=Adnan&last=Naqvi" https://saifnaqvi.com/methods -> Send update request (-X PUT) data

DELETE:
curl -X DELETE https://saifnaqvi.com/methods -> Send DELETE request (-X DELETE) data

For authentication (pages that require user and password)
curl -u saif:Sanqvi01 https://saifnaqvi.com/login

For downloading a file use output (-o)
curl -o file.jpg http://saifnaqvi.com/image1


